Schema Definitions

address-pool-service_schema:

Address Pool configuration data

vrfs: object

Enter VRF specific config mode

vrf: object[]

Specify VRF Name

object
vrf-name: string

none

ipv4: object

Enter IPv4 specific configuration

pools: object

IPv4 Pool Table

pool: object[]

IPv4 Pool name

object
excludes: object

Exclude addresses

exclude: object[]

First address in range

object
end-address: string

Last address in excluded range

start-address: string

First address in exclude range

address-ranges: object

address range for allocation

address-range: object[]

Specify first address in range

object
end-address: string

Last address of the range

start-address: string

Specify first address of the range

blocked: integer

Blocked flag

utilization-mark: object

Specify utilization mark

high: integer

Specify numerical value as percentage

range:"0..100" units:"percentage"
low: integer

Specify numerical value as percentage

range:"0..100" units:"percentage"
networks: object

Specify network for allocation

network: object[]

Network Prefix

object
ipv4-prefix: string

None

blocked: integer

Blocked flag

prefix-length: integer

Subnet Length for IPv4 subnet

default-router: string

Default Gateway for IPv4 subnet

pool-name: string

Enter the IPv4 Pool name

ipv6: object

Enter IPv6 specific mode

pools: object

IPv6 Pool Name

pool: object[]

Enter the IPv6 Pool name

object
excludes: object

Exclude IPv6 addresses / prefixes

exclude: object[]

None

object
end-address: string

Last address in exclude Range

start-address: string

First Address in IPv6 exclude range

prefix-length: integer

Enter the prefix-length for the Pool

prefix-ranges: object

Specify prefix range for allocation

prefix-range: object[]

None

object
start-prefix: string

First prefix of range

end-prefix: string

Last prefix of range

blocked: integer

Blocked flag

address-ranges: object

Specify address range for allocation

address-range: object[]

None

object
end-address: string

End Address of the range

start-address: string

Start address of the range

blocked: integer

Blocked flag

ipv6-pool-name: string

Enter the IPv6 Pool name

utilization-mark: object

Specify utilization mark

low-mark: integer

Specify numerical value as percentage

range:"0..100" units:"percentage"
high-mark: integer

Specify numerical value as percentage

range:"0..100" units:"percentage"
networks: object

Specify network for allocation

network: object[]

None

object
prefix: string

None

prefix-length: integer

Prefix length for the IPv6 Prefix

blocked: integer

Blocked flag

Example
{
  "vrfs": {
    "vrf": [
